Commentary Text: Rashid Khan to Ishan Kishan, out Ishan Kishan Run Out!! Excellent awareness from Bairstow. He even fooled Warner at slip, who gestured that it was not out. Kishan pats it towards cover and sets off, Pollard doesn't move and the young man has to turn back, run and puts in the dive as well. By this time, Bairstow had disturbed the stumps with his pad before the throw came but he ensured he uprooted one of the stumps with the ball in his hand. Kishan's dive meant the bat popped up and he was caught short of the crease. If the stumps were not uprooted, Kishan would have survived this. Ishan Kishan run out (Shankar/Bairstow) 17(21) [4s-2]

Commentary Text: Nabi to Rohit, out Caught by Hooda!! Hangs the ball in the air by bowling it slower, Rohit fails to control the hack and holes out at deep mid. He inner-halved the stroke and never timed it. The ball was tossed up at 82.9kph and all the power in the shot had to be invested by the batter. Commentary Text: Behrendorff to Manish Pandey, out Caught by Rohit!! Manish Pandey absolutely belted that but hits it straight into the hands of Rohit Sharma at mid-wicket. Sharp reflexes from Rohit though, a meter to the right or left of him would have been a boundary. But this sport is all about few centimeters. And this dismissal was just a vindication of that. It was a back of a length delivery on the stumps, Manish Pandey got a lot of willow behind the pull shot but when luck is not going your way you tend to find fielders. Commentary Text: Alzarri Joseph to Warner, out Bowled!! Wow! First ball in IPL cricket and Alzarri Joseph gets one of the most successful batsmen in the history of IPL. Stuff of dreams! It was on a fuller length and was wide of off, Warner throws his bat at it in a clumsy fashion perhaps some overconfidence. It clips his inside edge and comes back to disturb his timber. Warner b Alzarri Joseph 15(13) [4s-2]

Commentary Text: Rahul Chahar to Bairstow, out Caught by Bumrah!! No Bairstow show today. Perks of having a leggie in your team. Leg-spinners might go for a few runs but on most occasions will fetch you a wicket. Rahul Chahar has just done that and gives MI the first breakthrough. Serves the googly on a luring length outside off, Bairstow went for it, gets deceived by the flight and lost his shape completely. The outcome is a top-edge which spoons up to Bumrah at short third man, who takes the sitter. Bairstow c Bumrah b Rahul Chahar 16(10) [4s-3]
